# C-Data ONT Driver Frontend Implementation Plan

## Goal
Create a simple web-based frontend to interact with the [CDataJsonDriver](file:///Users/nobin/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/cdata_ont_tool/cdata_driver.py#6-168) python class. This will allow users to log in to the ONT device and perform ping tests through a user-friendly interface.

## User Review Required
> [!NOTE]
> This solution uses **FastAPI** for the backend and **vanilla HTML/JS** with **Tailwind CSS** (via CDN) for the frontend. This ensures the app is lightweight and easy to run without a complex build step.

## Proposed Changes

### Backend (`cdata_ont_tool`)
#### [NEW] [requirements.txt](file:///Users/nobin/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/cdata_ont_tool/requirements.txt)
- `fastapi`
- `uvicorn`
- `requests`
- `pydantic`

#### [NEW] [main.py](file:///Users/nobin/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/cdata_ont_tool/main.py)
- Setup FastAPI app.
- Serve static files (frontend).
- API Endpoints:
    - `POST /api/login`: Accepts IP, Username, Password. Initializes the [CDataJsonDriver](file:///Users/nobin/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/cdata_ont_tool/cdata_driver.py#6-168) and verifies login. Stores the driver instance in memory (simple state management).
    - `POST /api/ping`: Accepts target IP. Uses the stored driver instance to perform the ping.

### Frontend (`cdata_ont_tool/static`)
#### [NEW] [index.html](file:///Users/nobin/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/cdata_ont_tool/static/index.html)
- Single page application.
- **Login Section**: Form for Device IP, Username, Password.
- **Control Section**: Visible after login.
    - Ping Test form.
    - Output console to show results.
- Styling: Modern and clean using Tailwind CSS.
- Logic: Vanilla JavaScript to `fetch` data from the backend.

## Verification Plan
### Automated Tests
- Run `uvicorn main:app --reload`.
- Use `curl` to test `/api/login` and `/api/ping`.

### Manual Verification
- Open `http://localhost:8000` in browser.
- Enter credentials and test the login flow.
- Run a ping test and observe the output.
